WEBVTT

00:00.058 --> 00:01.343
<i>Previously on</i> Genius...

00:01.343 --> 00:04.236
I need help,
someone to work alongside me.

00:04.237 --> 00:06.407
Do you have someone particular in mind?

00:06.408 --> 00:09.218
Time is not absolute.

00:09.219 --> 00:11.965
(Besso gasps, Einstein laughs)

00:11.966 --> 00:13.371
Holy hell.

00:13.372 --> 00:16.084
I've devised my own
principle of relativity.

00:16.085 --> 00:18.544
It's the redefinition of the universe.

00:18.545 --> 00:20.460
This is what we've been chasing.

00:20.461 --> 00:21.481
You thanked Michele.

00:21.482 --> 00:22.472
EINSTEIN: Of course I thanked him.

00:22.473 --> 00:23.429
But I've helped you

00:23.430 --> 00:24.739
with so many papers,

00:24.740 --> 00:26.943
but you never thought to put
my name in any of them.

00:26.944 --> 00:28.284
It never occurred to me.

00:28.285 --> 00:29.242
Dr. Curie.

00:29.243 --> 00:30.361
You are to be awarded

00:30.362 --> 00:33.171
the 1903 Nobel Prize in Physics.

00:33.172 --> 00:35.086
Please inform the Nobel committee

00:35.087 --> 00:36.652
<i>that I will not accept the prize</i>

00:36.653 --> 00:37.929
<i>if they do not honor
my wife alongside me.</i>

00:37.930 --> 00:39.046
This patent clerk in Bern.

00:39.047 --> 00:40.963
He has cited us both in his paper on...

00:40.964 --> 00:43.262
Light quanta, yes, indeed. You see?

00:43.263 --> 00:44.315
Einstein.

00:44.316 --> 00:45.976
It's fascinating what one can deduce

00:45.977 --> 00:47.814
about a man just by knowing his name.

00:47.815 --> 00:50.305
LAUE: <i>I'm here at the behest
of Professor Max Planck.</i>

00:50.306 --> 00:51.423
The father of Prussian physics?

00:51.424 --> 00:53.099
Tell me, are you working
on anything else?

00:53.100 --> 00:53.757
Yes.

00:53.758 --> 00:56.890
LAUE: Herr Einstein, it's... genius.

